00:49.683 --> 00:52.684
<i>♪ I pass by that café ♪</i>

00:52.686 --> 00:55.788
<i>♪ Where we used to meet ♪</i>

00:55.790 --> 00:58.657
<i>♪ And as I walked by ♪</i>
[SNORING]

00:58.659 --> 01:02.061
<i>♪ A cozy scene meets my eye ♪</i>

01:02.063 --> 01:07.866
<i>♪ He's giving his new love that same ol' ♪</i>
[GROANS]

01:07.868 --> 01:12.471
<i>♪ I have to stop</i>
<i>She's pretty, it's true ♪</i>

01:12.473 --> 01:14.273
[GROANING]

01:14.275 --> 01:20.145
<i>♪ And it looks like she's trying</i>
<i>real hard to please too ♪</i>

01:20.147 --> 01:23.649
[GROANING CONTINUES]
<i>♪ Oh, it's tempting to think ♪</i>

01:23.651 --> 01:26.385
<i>♪ I should step in for her ♪</i>

01:26.387 --> 01:31.490
<i>♪ I could tell her</i>
<i>just what he'll do ♪</i>

01:31.492 --> 01:35.828
<i>♪ Someday he'll break your heart ♪</i>
[WATER STOPS RUNNING]

01:37.363 --> 01:41.633
<i>♪ Just the way he broke mine ♪</i>

01:43.937 --> 01:47.840
<i>♪ I know that's assured ♪♪</i>

02:05.358 --> 02:06.925
You're awake.

02:06.927 --> 02:09.328
Who the fuck are you?

02:09.330 --> 02:12.264
You left your wallet and keys
at the bar I work at.

02:13.299 --> 02:16.635
You know,
after you got your ass kicked.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.937
Catch.

02:18.939 --> 02:22.141
Get the fuck out.
Ah, not a morning person?

02:22.143 --> 02:23.876
No.

02:23.878 --> 02:26.078
How about I get dressed first?

02:36.723 --> 02:38.290
[WATER RUNNING]

02:48.001 --> 02:50.435
<i>[WOMAN NARRATING]</i>
<i>If you're gonna tell a story,</i>

02:50.437 --> 02:54.039
<i>it's best to tell it</i>
<i>straight and true.</i>

02:54.041 --> 02:57.609
<i>But what if the truth</i>
<i>ain't straight?</i>

02:57.611 --> 03:00.812
<i>This here's the story</i>
<i>of two sisters torn apart.</i>

03:01.681 --> 03:05.150
<i>The question is: By what?</i>

03:06.386 --> 03:07.953
<i>Fate?</i>

03:09.022 --> 03:10.589
<i>God?</i>

03:11.691 --> 03:13.792
<i>Me?</i>

03:13.794 --> 03:15.360
<i>Maybe.</i>

03:22.101 --> 03:25.237
<i>I found him last night</i>
<i>outside the bar I work at.</i>

03:25.239 --> 03:28.707
<i>♪♪ [GUITAR BALLAD]</i>

03:32.545 --> 03:36.548
<i>♪♪ [MAN VOCALIZING]</i>

03:36.550 --> 03:41.887
<i>♪ Out here all alone ♪</i>

03:45.725 --> 03:49.228
<i>♪ It's time for thinkin' ♪</i>

03:49.230 --> 03:52.764
<i>♪ And dreamin' about</i>
<i>being gone ♪</i>

03:59.172 --> 04:02.908
<i>♪♪ [VOCALIZING]</i>

04:02.910 --> 04:06.912
<i>♪ I call this song my own ♪</i>

04:12.785 --> 04:16.221
<i>♪ I sing it for myself ♪</i>

04:16.223 --> 04:21.392
<i>♪ Just a song before I go ♪</i>

04:25.665 --> 04:28.200
<i>♪ And I remember ♪♪</i>

04:28.202 --> 04:30.535
How many times we got
to keep doing this, Wayne?

04:30.537 --> 04:33.171
Always trying to make me look
bad in front of my people.

04:33.173 --> 04:34.606
- Hey!
- [GROANS]

04:34.608 --> 04:37.175
- Get off him!
- Step off, bitch!

05:00.633 --> 05:02.701
[COUGHING]

05:07.040 --> 05:08.707
[GROANS]

05:10.310 --> 05:13.011
Hey, man, you all right?
[GROANS]

05:13.013 --> 05:15.681
Want me to call the cops?
[GROANS]

05:17.717 --> 05:19.584
Tell me what you want me to do.

05:19.586 --> 05:22.754
Learn how to mind
your own fucking business.

05:22.756 --> 05:24.890
[GROANING]

05:36.069 --> 05:38.904
<i>[WOMAN]</i>
<i>♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah-ah, oh ♪</i>

05:42.909 --> 05:46.511
<i>♪ Ah-ah, ah, ah, ah-ah, oh ♪</i>

05:49.148 --> 05:51.450
<i>[WOMAN NARRATING] The story
really starts when I was 15...</i>

05:51.452 --> 05:53.385
<i>and my mama got cancer.</i>

05:54.921 --> 05:57.522
<i>One day we're all sittin'</i>
<i>around her hospital bed...</i>

05:57.524 --> 06:00.859
<i>while they drained her blood out</i>
<i>like a bunch of mosquitoes.</i>

06:02.929 --> 06:05.697
<i>Next it's just me</i>
<i>and my sister...</i>

06:07.300 --> 06:09.768
<i>figuring out the world</i>
<i>for ourselves.</i>

06:12.839 --> 06:16.608
<i>♪♪ [CONTINUES, INDISTINCT]</i>

06:49.909 --> 06:53.812
<i>Once upon a time, we could hide our
pain by slipping into a costume.</i>

06:54.480 --> 06:56.515
<i>Liz, a princess,</i>

06:56.517 --> 06:58.350
<i>and me, Wonder Girl.</i>

06:58.352 --> 07:02.687
<i>But after Mama died,</i>
<i>things got complicated.</i>

07:02.689 --> 07:05.824
<i>I could get high a dozen times</i>
<i>and stop whenever I wanted,</i>

07:05.826 --> 07:08.360
<i>but for Liz,</i>

07:08.362 --> 07:10.529
<i>it wasn't like that.</i>

07:12.432 --> 07:15.333
<i>There's people you miss</i>
<i>when they're gone.</i>

07:15.335 --> 07:19.571
<i>Then there's the people</i>
<i>that's so tangled up with you...</i>

07:19.573 --> 07:24.342
<i>that losing them means cutting off a piece
of your own flesh right along with them.</i>

07:25.645 --> 07:27.712
<i>You cut off</i>
<i>that much of yourself,</i>

07:27.714 --> 07:30.182
<i>it's bound to leave</i>
<i>some scars.</i>

07:44.397 --> 07:45.964
[WAYNE] Get in.

08:01.347 --> 08:03.248
[KEYS RATTLE]
[ENGINE STOPS]

08:05.618 --> 08:09.354
Thanks... for bringing
my shit back.

08:09.356 --> 08:12.891
Not much I can really do with
six bucks and a military I.D.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.130
See you around.

08:21.100 --> 08:22.734
I'm Charlotte, by the way.

08:31.244 --> 08:32.811
[ENGINE STARTS]

08:54.433 --> 08:56.268
<i>♪♪ [RADIO: COUNTRY]</i>

09:07.446 --> 09:09.247
Come on, Shirley.

09:12.485 --> 09:14.119
Ah, Jesus.

09:20.960 --> 09:22.527
Hey!

09:25.965 --> 09:27.832
I need a favor.

09:30.770 --> 09:32.370
Hey!

09:39.612 --> 09:41.179
[GRUNTS]

09:41.181 --> 09:43.515
I need to borrow your car.

09:44.317 --> 09:45.884
No.

09:45.886 --> 09:48.987
But, uh, that's what friends do.

09:48.989 --> 09:50.555
They borrow things.

09:53.192 --> 09:55.393
Oh, you have a friend now, huh?

09:55.395 --> 09:58.597
- When did that happen?
- When I needed a car.

09:58.599 --> 10:00.865
Get out.
Well, how about a ride?

10:06.272 --> 10:08.473
Look, um,

10:08.475 --> 10:10.642
my mom's not doing so good.

10:10.644 --> 10:13.378
I need to go get my sister,

10:13.380 --> 10:15.647
bring her home.

10:20.386 --> 10:22.153
I'll pay you.

10:31.430 --> 10:32.998
$200.

10:34.600 --> 10:36.167
Everything I got.

10:44.343 --> 10:46.277
[SIGHS]

10:51.350 --> 10:53.151
Let's go.

11:02.194 --> 11:04.162
Where we going?

11:04.164 --> 11:05.730
Up Sugar Mountain.

11:07.633 --> 11:10.001
After this, you can stop
coming around, okay?

11:10.003 --> 11:12.103
Yeah.

11:12.105 --> 11:16.541
<i>[FEMALE VOCALISTS]</i>
<i>♪ Runnin' from the devil ♪</i>

11:16.543 --> 11:21.579
<i>♪ 'Cause running's all I know ♪</i>

11:21.581 --> 11:26.217
<i>♪ Ran so far, I got lost ♪</i>

11:26.219 --> 11:30.622
<i>♪ And so I ran some more ♪</i>

11:30.624 --> 11:36.194
<i>♪ Jesus rides ahead of me ♪</i>

11:36.196 --> 11:40.331
<i>♪ But the devil's</i>
<i>gainin' ground ♪</i>

11:40.333 --> 11:43.268
<i>♪ So I'm runnin'</i>
<i>Yes, I'm runnin' ♪</i>

11:43.270 --> 11:45.570
<i>[CHARLOTTE NARRATING]</i>
<i>When you're alone in this world,</i>

11:45.572 --> 11:48.206
<i>you learn</i>
<i>to find help anywhere,</i>

11:48.208 --> 11:50.041
<i>any way you can,</i>

11:50.043 --> 11:52.544
<i>including bending the truth</i>
<i>about your own dead mama.</i>

11:52.546 --> 11:54.446
<i>♪ Yes, I'm runnin' ♪</i>

11:54.448 --> 12:00.051
<i>The trick is to find someone who might
just be worse off than you are.</i>

12:00.053 --> 12:02.787
<i>They're the ones</i>
<i>who've got nothing to lose.</i>

12:23.542 --> 12:26.945
<i>I haven't seen or heard from Liz</i>
<i>in over a year.</i>

12:26.947 --> 12:29.814
<i>Then a letter came in the mail.</i>

12:29.816 --> 12:32.517
<i>She wrote that she missed me,</i>

12:32.519 --> 12:36.354
<i>that she was sober and living at
a church up on Sugar Mountain.</i>

12:38.758 --> 12:41.426
<i>Needed me to come get her</i>
<i>right away.</i>

12:42.128 --> 12:44.095
<i>Why?</i>

12:44.097 --> 12:45.930
<i>She didn't say.</i>

12:45.932 --> 12:48.900
<i>Just that she was scared</i>
<i>and needed to come home.</i>

12:52.404 --> 12:54.439
What is this place?

12:54.441 --> 12:56.141
A church, I think.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.383
Goddamn it.

13:12.758 --> 13:16.327
[NO AUDIO]

13:48.227 --> 13:51.763
[MEN] ♪ Let it shine ♪

13:51.765 --> 13:54.966
♪ ♪ [DRUMS, GUITAR]
[CONGREGATION WHOOPING]

14:08.414 --> 14:10.548
[MEN]
♪ This little light of mine ♪

14:10.550 --> 14:12.717
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

14:12.719 --> 14:15.019
♪ This little light of mine ♪

14:15.021 --> 14:17.622
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

14:17.624 --> 14:19.490
♪ This little light of mine ♪

14:19.492 --> 14:21.559
♪ I'm gonna let it shine ♪

14:21.561 --> 14:24.796
♪ Let it shine,
let it shine, let it shine ♪

14:24.798 --> 14:30.235
♪ I'm gonna let it shine,
let it shine, let it shine ♪♪

14:34.473 --> 14:36.374
[MAN] Thank you.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.314
All right.

14:43.316 --> 14:44.883
All right.

14:49.688 --> 14:52.490
Welcome.
[CONGREGATION] Welcome!

14:52.492 --> 14:54.325
[WHOOPING]
[WOMAN] Yeah!

14:57.129 --> 15:00.298
This Bible don't lie.
[MAN] No, it don't!

15:00.300 --> 15:01.866
[WOMAN] No!

15:01.868 --> 15:05.169
It don't do nothin'
but tell God's plain truth...

15:05.171 --> 15:06.804
every word.

15:06.806 --> 15:09.040
Every word.

15:09.042 --> 15:12.110
You don't get to pick and
choose, now, honey, do ya?

15:12.112 --> 15:14.812
This ain't no ice cream parlor.

15:15.915 --> 15:18.149
What do you like,
Smiling Bobby? Vanilla?

15:18.151 --> 15:19.717
No!

15:19.719 --> 15:21.886
How about bubblegum?

15:21.888 --> 15:24.322
It ain't like that, is it?
No, sir.

15:24.324 --> 15:26.958
[WOMAN] No, it ain't!
[MAN] He knows it, Brother Bill.

15:26.960 --> 15:30.461
You're either all in...
or you're out.

15:30.463 --> 15:32.030
- [WOMAN] That's right!
- You're out!

15:32.032 --> 15:37.402
You are out into that lake of
fire to burn for eternity.

15:37.404 --> 15:40.138
But it don't have to be that way.
Do it, Brother Sherman?

15:40.140 --> 15:41.673
No, sir.
No, it don't.

15:41.675 --> 15:44.375
And why is that?
Why is that?

15:44.377 --> 15:46.878
That's because
Jesus sent us the Holy Ghost.

15:46.880 --> 15:50.581
But there's only one way to
receive that spirit, isn't there?

15:51.884 --> 15:54.385
We got to be in one accord.

15:54.387 --> 15:57.388
Are we in one accord?
[CONGREGATION] Yes!

15:57.390 --> 15:58.589
Amen!

15:58.591 --> 16:01.059
Bless your name, holy Jesus.

16:01.061 --> 16:03.194
Satan's sheddin'
big ol' tears tonight.

16:03.196 --> 16:05.730
[CONGREGATION] Yeah!

16:06.565 --> 16:08.933
[RATTLING]

16:12.638 --> 16:14.238
He's a big boy, ain't he?

16:15.441 --> 16:17.909
I call him Satan,
'cause he's so big and mean.

16:17.911 --> 16:20.611
[RATTLING CONTINUES]

16:22.414 --> 16:26.751
It's these deadly serpents the Lord
sent us to handle... without fear.

16:26.753 --> 16:28.553
[RATTLING CONTINUES]

16:28.555 --> 16:32.123
Our hearts are filled
with the Holy Ghost. Mmm.

16:32.125 --> 16:34.492
Get on up here, Brother Cole.

16:34.494 --> 16:36.427
Satan wants to talk to you.

16:37.196 --> 16:42.900
♪ ♪ [DRUMS, GUITAR]

16:43.769 --> 16:46.637
♪ ♪ [MEN SINGING, INDISTINCT]

16:46.639 --> 16:49.640
[CONGREGATION CHATTERING]

17:02.821 --> 17:05.589
Hey!

17:09.428 --> 17:11.762
[RATTLING]

17:33.786 --> 17:36.120
Where is she?

17:36.122 --> 17:38.389
I don't know.
[GRUNTS]

17:41.093 --> 17:43.227
I'll be in the car.

17:46.398 --> 17:49.867
<i>[CHARLOTTE NARRATING] You hear stories
trickling down the mountain...</i>

17:49.869 --> 17:53.337
<i>of people up here following</i>
<i>their own sort of laws.</i>

17:53.339 --> 17:56.340
<i>Old laws. You know?</i>

17:56.342 --> 18:00.144
<i>The kind where blood gets shed</i>
<i>when they're broke.</i>

18:00.146 --> 18:03.648
<i>Cops don't even come up here,</i>

18:03.650 --> 18:08.486
<i>let alone a city girl</i>
<i>poking around, asking questions.</i>

18:14.526 --> 18:16.227
How you doing?

18:17.229 --> 18:19.297
How can we help you?

18:19.299 --> 18:21.966
Well, I was wondering...

18:21.968 --> 18:23.668
Mm-hmm?

18:25.070 --> 18:27.705
I was wondering
if I could join your church.

18:29.408 --> 18:32.577
And what about your gentleman friend?
He wanna join too?

18:33.278 --> 18:36.180
Oh, uh, that's my daddy.

18:36.182 --> 18:38.883
Oh, well, your daddy
don't seem too interested.

18:38.885 --> 18:41.018
He has problems with his nerves.

18:41.020 --> 18:42.687
Socially.

18:43.355 --> 18:45.323
Hmm.

18:45.325 --> 18:47.391
We're not so easy to find.

18:47.393 --> 18:48.960
I know.

18:48.962 --> 18:52.096
But, uh, people talk, you know.

18:52.098 --> 18:53.898
No, I don't.

18:55.601 --> 18:58.202
Excuse me.
Wait.

19:00.405 --> 19:02.073
My dad, um...

19:04.476 --> 19:07.011
He has a problem
with the bottle, you see.

19:07.013 --> 19:09.680
And... I've tried everything,

19:09.682 --> 19:12.483
short of kicking his butt
out of the house.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.452
And, uh...

19:16.522 --> 19:18.089
I'm sorry.

19:18.091 --> 19:21.325
You're all right.
You're fine.

19:22.594 --> 19:24.562
Now, what's your name?

19:24.564 --> 19:26.130
Rachel.

19:27.132 --> 19:29.600
All right, Rachel, I'm Billy.

19:29.602 --> 19:31.169
Now, listen.

19:31.171 --> 19:33.237
This mountain,
it gets awfully dark at night,

19:33.239 --> 19:35.473
easy to lose track
of where you're at.

19:35.475 --> 19:38.476
This ain't territory
you wanna get lost in.

19:38.478 --> 19:41.112
I can't just let you up and join.
But...

19:41.114 --> 19:44.015
But what I can do is offer
you a bed for the evening,

19:44.017 --> 19:46.584
and tomorrow you and your
daddy can take a look around,

19:46.586 --> 19:49.253
see if what people's
been saying is the truth.

19:50.923 --> 19:53.691
Plenty of folks out there speaking
with forked tongues these days,

19:53.693 --> 19:55.326
if you know what I mean.

20:01.600 --> 20:03.234
Your dad?

20:13.712 --> 20:15.947
I'll pay you another $200.

20:15.949 --> 20:17.648
When we get back.

20:23.288 --> 20:25.756
Take care of yourself, kid.

20:25.758 --> 20:28.059
[ENGINE STARTS]

20:35.834 --> 20:38.035
[CAR DRIVES AWAY]

20:40.672 --> 20:42.406
Right this way.

20:44.610 --> 20:46.611
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:47.946 --> 20:49.847
Where's your father?

20:50.882 --> 20:53.651
He forgot something in the car.

21:04.363 --> 21:07.598
- Hey.
- You must be Rachel's father.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.166
Wayne.

21:11.436 --> 21:13.271
I'm Sister Sheila.

21:14.373 --> 21:17.041
Y'all need anything else,
don't hesitate to ask.

21:17.776 --> 21:19.577
We'll be fine.

21:21.613 --> 21:23.180
Good night.

21:23.849 --> 21:25.416
Good night.

21:37.062 --> 21:40.431
How'd your sister get
caught up in all this shit?

21:43.268 --> 21:45.369
I... I don't know.

21:50.776 --> 21:53.744
You know what you're
getting yourself into?

21:53.746 --> 21:55.880
Just give me the day.

21:59.685 --> 22:02.253
I always hated going to church.

22:22.207 --> 22:23.774
Shit.

22:23.776 --> 22:26.644
[OWL HOOTING]

22:39.758 --> 22:41.592
Charlotte, let me in.

22:42.427 --> 22:44.795
Charlotte!
Charlotte!

22:44.797 --> 22:46.597
Charlotte!
Charlotte, it's me!

22:46.599 --> 22:48.165
Charlotte, it's me!
Just open the door!

22:48.167 --> 22:50.735
Charlotte.
Charlotte, you want me to die?

22:50.737 --> 22:55.439
[PANTING]

23:08.987 --> 23:12.089
We let Jesus
and his beliefs guide us,

23:12.091 --> 23:15.626
not only in our hearts
but also in our hands.

23:17.496 --> 23:21.899
Up here, we live, breathe
and sleep the Word,

23:21.901 --> 23:24.168
submit ourselves to it.

23:25.837 --> 23:29.407
We have addicts
and former convicts...

23:29.409 --> 23:32.877
forgotten souls that other
churches would have turned away.

23:32.879 --> 23:35.713
But we're all family in God's eyes.

23:35.715 --> 23:37.281
Hello.

23:38.517 --> 23:40.050
That's Smiling Bobby.

23:40.052 --> 23:41.986
Brother Billy gave him his name.

23:41.988 --> 23:45.089
Said God stuck a smile on
him and called it a day.

23:45.091 --> 23:46.657
[LAUGHS]

23:49.194 --> 23:53.464
Brother Edgar, your commitment
to Jesus Christ starts today.

23:54.199 --> 23:55.900
Your baptism truly is...

23:55.902 --> 23:57.902
your new beginning.

23:57.904 --> 24:03.073
An obedience to the wonderful,
almighty, powerful word of God.

24:03.075 --> 24:06.477
And in commandment with our
Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ,

24:06.479 --> 24:10.781
we baptize this brother...
in the name of Lord Jesus.

24:12.717 --> 24:15.586
[ALL WHOOPING]

24:15.588 --> 24:17.321
Sweet Jesus!

24:19.357 --> 24:21.826
[BROTHER BILLY]
How do you do it, Jesus?

24:21.828 --> 24:24.395
How do you give us this strength?
Whoo!

24:24.397 --> 24:26.130
Hallelujah, brother.

24:57.696 --> 24:59.296
Hey.

24:59.298 --> 25:02.366
You gonna stay the day,
you got to work the day.

25:02.368 --> 25:03.968
That's the rule.

25:06.571 --> 25:09.807
[WOMEN]
♪ I got Jesus on my mind ♪

25:09.809 --> 25:14.211
♪ When you see me comin',
I got Jesus on my mind ♪

25:14.213 --> 25:18.649
♪ I got Jesus, Jesus on my mind ♪

25:18.651 --> 25:23.087
♪ When you see me prayin',
I got Jesus on my mind ♪

25:23.089 --> 25:27.525
♪ When you see me prayin',
I got Jesus on my mind ♪

25:27.527 --> 25:31.929
♪ When you see me prayin',
I got Jesus on my mind ♪

25:48.313 --> 25:49.880
Need some help?

25:50.815 --> 25:52.383
Sure.

25:57.088 --> 25:58.956
Can I ask you something?

26:01.159 --> 26:02.993
Can you leave?

26:02.995 --> 26:06.463
You know, if you decide
this isn't right for you.

26:08.333 --> 26:11.635
[CHUCKLES]
Honey, this ain't no prison.

26:17.576 --> 26:20.477
You know if someone called
Liz O'Neil ever lived here?

26:20.479 --> 26:22.780
Mm, not that I know of.

26:22.782 --> 26:26.417
Are you sure?
'Cause she told me that she did.

26:26.419 --> 26:30.921
Hey. Ain't you supposed
to be cleaning the showers?

26:30.923 --> 26:32.790
I finished with that,
so I thought I'd...

26:32.792 --> 26:34.558
You thought you'd what?

26:34.560 --> 26:36.260
I'm sorry, Brother Sherman.

26:36.262 --> 26:38.762
I'll... I'll go see if Sister
Nancy needs extra help.

26:38.764 --> 26:40.331
Good.

26:42.801 --> 26:45.269
How you doing...

26:45.271 --> 26:46.870
with all this?

26:46.872 --> 26:48.439
I'm all right.

26:49.441 --> 26:52.042
It must be quite a shock.

26:52.044 --> 26:53.911
City girl like yourself.

26:55.647 --> 26:57.681
I'm doing just fine.

27:40.225 --> 27:41.792
Come on, son.

27:41.794 --> 27:43.794
Back and the front.
The back and the front.

27:43.796 --> 27:45.796
Come on now.
Wash 'em.

27:45.798 --> 27:49.566
<i>♪♪ [STEREO, GOSPEL]</i>

27:49.568 --> 27:51.735
Marine Corps, huh?

27:52.904 --> 27:54.972
Iraq?

27:54.974 --> 27:56.573
Afghanistan.

27:57.409 --> 27:59.410
Three tours.

28:00.345 --> 28:02.446
Look at this.
Look at this.

28:04.182 --> 28:06.417
United States Army.

28:06.419 --> 28:08.952
First Battalion, 101st Airborne.

28:08.954 --> 28:11.021
Vietnam.

28:11.023 --> 28:12.623
Hooah.

28:14.125 --> 28:15.793
Hooah.

28:15.795 --> 28:17.361
Come on now.

28:18.329 --> 28:20.698
Do the work. Do the work.
Come on now.

29:20.625 --> 29:22.960
"There is no fear in love."
[GASPS]

29:24.796 --> 29:26.730
How true.

29:26.732 --> 29:28.699
Excuse me, Rachel.

29:31.669 --> 29:33.470
[KEYS RATTLING]

29:40.245 --> 29:41.812
Come on.

29:43.248 --> 29:44.815
You're fine.

29:56.795 --> 29:58.562
[RATTLING]

29:58.564 --> 30:00.664
Let me out.
All right. Come on. Come on, girl.

30:00.666 --> 30:04.434
Come on. Hey, hey, hey, hey.
[RATTLING CONTINUES]

30:29.227 --> 30:31.728
When you handle a deadly serpent,

30:31.730 --> 30:33.630
all your pain,

30:34.699 --> 30:38.702
all your fears just...
disappear.

30:40.038 --> 30:42.773
It's just you, the serpent
and the Holy Ghost.

30:45.510 --> 30:47.945
Only one way to conquer your enemy.

30:49.480 --> 30:51.582
That's to love him.

31:12.503 --> 31:14.371
[SIGHS]

31:17.408 --> 31:22.980
[BELL TOLLING]

31:22.982 --> 31:24.781
You comin'?

31:24.783 --> 31:27.017
[BELL CONTINUES]
Yeah.

31:42.166 --> 31:46.403
♪ ♪ [GOSPEL]

31:50.008 --> 31:52.009
Yeah!

31:52.011 --> 31:55.045
Whoo!
[CONGREGATION WHOOPING]

32:02.086 --> 32:03.654
Yeah!

32:14.098 --> 32:16.199
Yes, sir.

32:16.201 --> 32:19.403
I am hot for God tonight.

32:19.405 --> 32:21.438
[MAN] Yes, sir, Brother Billy!

32:21.440 --> 32:23.607
If you ain't hot for God, honey,

32:23.609 --> 32:25.742
then just get
as cold as you can get.

32:25.744 --> 32:28.211
We'll know what side
of the fence you're on.

32:29.347 --> 32:31.982
[RATTLING]

32:37.488 --> 32:39.923
If the gospel's
good enough to live by,

32:39.925 --> 32:42.259
then it's good enough to die by.

32:42.261 --> 32:44.227
[RATTLING CONTINUES]

32:44.229 --> 32:45.796
And I'm ready.

32:47.832 --> 32:49.733
I'm willin', Lord.

32:50.702 --> 32:53.737
[RATTLING CONTINUES]

32:53.739 --> 32:56.907
[RATTLING GROWS LOUDER]

33:02.747 --> 33:05.282
[RATTLING SOFTENS]
Oh.

33:08.252 --> 33:11.221
I ain't afraid to be judged
for the deeds I've done.

33:14.092 --> 33:15.959
Are you?

33:17.528 --> 33:19.463
Praise.

33:30.608 --> 33:32.442
[RATTLING]

33:35.046 --> 33:37.681
[RATTLING GROWS LOUDER]

33:41.753 --> 33:43.320
[WOMAN LAUGHS]

33:44.589 --> 33:47.691
[SCATTERED LAUGHTER]

33:47.693 --> 33:49.693
How about a song?

33:49.695 --> 33:52.662
[ALL WHOOPING]

33:52.664 --> 33:57.734
♪ Well, he didn't have to do it,
but he did ♪

33:59.504 --> 34:03.874
♪ He didn't have to love me,
but he did ♪

34:03.876 --> 34:06.643
♪ Brought me up,
put me on my way ♪

34:06.645 --> 34:09.246
♪ Woke me up and I'm here to stay ♪

34:09.248 --> 34:13.550
♪ He didn't have to do it,
but he did ♪♪

34:17.588 --> 34:19.389
I love my wife.

34:20.458 --> 34:22.025
With all my heart.

34:22.793 --> 34:25.462
She's obedient,

34:25.464 --> 34:27.496
kind.

34:27.498 --> 34:29.533
I am truly blessed.

34:33.271 --> 34:34.838
But...

34:38.443 --> 34:40.710
I have a demon inside of me.

34:42.513 --> 34:44.848
It's invaded my mind...

34:49.454 --> 34:52.922
with thoughts of other women.

34:55.493 --> 34:57.594
Sexual thoughts.

35:02.033 --> 35:04.401
I-I-I've prayed on it.

35:06.637 --> 35:08.205
Alone.

35:08.207 --> 35:10.807
- And with my wife.
- [SOBS]

35:13.644 --> 35:17.047
[SNIFFLES]
But it's no good.

35:17.682 --> 35:20.917
[CRYING]

35:20.919 --> 35:22.185
[GROANS]

35:50.915 --> 35:51.982
[GASPS]

35:56.087 --> 35:57.654
[GRUNTS]

36:00.057 --> 36:03.493
God... Je...
Holy Ghost, come in me.

36:05.830 --> 36:06.930
[GROANS]

36:17.475 --> 36:19.042
That's enough.

36:22.146 --> 36:23.713
That's enough.

36:38.963 --> 36:41.198
God bless you, Brother Sherman.

36:43.000 --> 36:45.135
God bless this church.

37:07.258 --> 37:09.893
What the hell did you do?

37:09.895 --> 37:13.697
- Get your shit and let's go.
- You backin' out on me?

37:13.699 --> 37:16.633
You lookin' for something
that ain't here.

37:16.635 --> 37:19.302
Yeah, well, you're just
looking for a fucking drink.

37:19.304 --> 37:20.870
Fuckin'...

37:27.044 --> 37:29.179
Go get your drink, Wayne.

37:30.047 --> 37:31.915
Get the fuck out...

37:37.955 --> 37:39.522
[WAYNE] Fuck it.

37:47.331 --> 37:49.366
[BROTHER BILLY] You're a
Southern boy, aren't ya?

37:49.368 --> 37:53.103
Let me guess.
Louisiana.

37:53.105 --> 37:56.473
- New Orleans.
- New Orleans. Whoo!

37:56.475 --> 37:59.242
Devil sure runs wild
down there, don't he?

37:59.244 --> 38:01.578
Think I even ran with him
a time or two.

38:03.748 --> 38:05.548
You don't seem surprised.

38:05.550 --> 38:08.618
I think I got you
pretty well figured out.

38:08.620 --> 38:10.186
You do, huh?

38:10.188 --> 38:13.089
Yeah.
Hide up here,

38:13.091 --> 38:15.492
feed these people bullshit.

38:16.594 --> 38:18.662
You think that, huh?

38:18.664 --> 38:22.332
Just one big power play,
and you get off on it.

38:23.801 --> 38:25.368
Oh.

38:26.704 --> 38:28.438
Well, maybe you're right.

38:28.440 --> 38:31.741
Sometimes I forget what this
must look like from the outside.

38:35.279 --> 38:38.415
You know that Neil Young
song "Sugar Mountain"?

38:38.417 --> 38:39.983
What?
You know that song?

38:40.851 --> 38:43.987
- Yeah.
- I like Neil Young.

38:43.989 --> 38:45.655
Used to.

38:45.657 --> 38:48.525
And that song's
all about being young forever.

38:50.261 --> 38:53.263
♪ Oh, to live on ♪

38:53.265 --> 38:55.498
♪ Sugar Mountain ♪

38:55.500 --> 38:57.534
♪ With the... ♪
[HUMMING]

38:57.536 --> 38:59.102
I can't remember all the words.

38:59.104 --> 39:00.870
But I do remember...

39:00.872 --> 39:03.006
♪ You can't be 20 ♪

39:03.008 --> 39:05.442
♪ On Sugar Mountain ♪

39:05.444 --> 39:09.679
♪ Though you're thinking that
you're leaving there too soon ♪

39:11.148 --> 39:14.284
♪ Leaving there too soon ♪

39:17.188 --> 39:19.489
I was 19 when my daddy died.

39:19.491 --> 39:23.326
It was a jet black, son of a bitch timber.
Got him real good on the arm.

39:23.328 --> 39:25.395
He was dead in 15 minutes.

39:25.397 --> 39:27.464
Fifteen minutes.

39:27.466 --> 39:31.568
I was right there with him, holding
his hand when his heart stopped cold.

39:32.970 --> 39:36.339
He'd have killed me if he knew
I was listening to Neil Young.

39:36.341 --> 39:38.575
Drinking beer.
Lots of beer.

39:38.577 --> 39:40.877
Sleeping with women.
Lots of women.

39:40.879 --> 39:42.579
[LAUGHS]

39:44.248 --> 39:47.684
We're not that different,
Brother Wayne.

39:47.686 --> 39:49.753
I know it might feel that way.

39:51.422 --> 39:52.989
Yeah.

39:56.761 --> 39:59.095
Anyway, I just wanted to come
down here and apologize...

39:59.097 --> 40:00.897
for forcing that snake on you.

40:00.899 --> 40:03.099
That was bullshit, and I'm sorry.

40:04.101 --> 40:06.169
You take care of yourself.

40:06.904 --> 40:08.772
Hey.

40:08.774 --> 40:11.608
You really believe in all of this?

40:12.710 --> 40:14.677
On my daddy's grave.

41:02.593 --> 41:04.227
[GRUNTS]

41:10.100 --> 41:11.668
[GRUNTS]

41:12.336 --> 41:16.272
[MUTTERING]

41:21.679 --> 41:23.746
[SOBBING]

41:23.748 --> 41:27.450
[SHOUTING, INDISTINCT]
Shh.

41:27.452 --> 41:29.152
Shh, shh. Hey.

41:29.154 --> 41:31.020
[COUGHING]

41:31.022 --> 41:33.756
[GRUNTING]
Shh.

41:46.470 --> 41:48.705
Shh.

41:48.707 --> 41:50.773
We'll leave in the morning.

42:14.598 --> 42:16.699
I thought I smelled smoke.

42:16.701 --> 42:19.102
Sorry. It's not allowed
or something?

42:19.104 --> 42:21.571
May I?
Sure.

42:25.943 --> 42:29.812
Can't smoke cigarettes, drink,
wear makeup, any of that.

42:29.814 --> 42:33.650
A pretty girl like you shouldn't
hide behind your lipstick anyway.

42:33.652 --> 42:36.085
Ah, it's fine.
Finish it up.

42:45.930 --> 42:48.131
Now, I'm gonna help
your daddy heal,

42:48.133 --> 42:51.367
and then I'm gonna help you.
Oh, yeah?

42:58.042 --> 42:59.676
Good girl.

43:03.380 --> 43:06.849
Now, you entered God's country,

43:06.851 --> 43:09.152
and he brought you
up here for a reason.

43:09.154 --> 43:12.255
When you figure it out,
give me a holler.

43:17.094 --> 43:18.661
Liz O'Neil.

43:19.930 --> 43:21.965
Know where she is?

43:21.967 --> 43:24.000
- Who's that?
- A friend.

43:24.002 --> 43:26.669
Part of this church. She's the
one that told me to come here.

43:26.671 --> 43:28.471
Huh.

43:28.473 --> 43:31.341
Sorry. I never heard of your friend.
Wrong church maybe.

43:32.843 --> 43:34.911
Church of One Accord?

43:34.913 --> 43:36.679
You're at it.

43:57.134 --> 44:00.737
[CHATTERING]
[LAUGHING]

44:14.852 --> 44:16.586
[GROANS]

47:35.752 --> 47:37.320
Liz?

47:39.690 --> 47:44.060
[SMILING BOBBY]
♪ Many burdens that we have to bear ♪

47:44.062 --> 47:46.529
Brother Bill, you in?

47:47.898 --> 47:52.368
♪ But there's a prayer bell
at the Lord's right hand ♪

47:52.370 --> 47:57.506
♪ Give it a ring
and he will understand ♪

48:00.744 --> 48:03.512
♪♪ [WHISTLING]

48:09.486 --> 48:10.953
[CLICKS]

48:17.327 --> 48:19.228
[SIGHS]

48:20.831 --> 48:22.565
Thank you, God.

48:24.434 --> 48:29.772
♪ Prayer bells on heaven
Oh, how sweetly they ring ♪

48:29.774 --> 48:31.908
They're ringing today, Father.

48:33.210 --> 48:38.347
♪ Sendin' a message
unto Jesus, our king ♪ ♪

48:38.349 --> 48:40.249
Thank you, Jesus.

48:40.851 --> 48:42.752
Another precious day.

48:47.791 --> 48:49.458
♪♪ [WHISTLING]

49:20.390 --> 49:22.992
I know you don't believe in
what we're doing up here.

49:24.728 --> 49:26.762
You don't know anything about me.

49:27.497 --> 49:29.665
I know more than you think.

49:31.234 --> 49:33.970
My world wasn't always this place.

49:42.212 --> 49:44.747
[ERRATIC BREATHING]

49:47.384 --> 49:50.019
Take your daughter and go.

49:59.830 --> 50:01.998
You don't belong here.

50:24.621 --> 50:26.188
Where'd you get this?

50:26.190 --> 50:28.257
Billy's cabin.

50:31.361 --> 50:32.928
Hey.

50:33.930 --> 50:36.132
Go to the cabin now!

50:41.938 --> 50:43.005
[DOOR CLOSES]

50:43.007 --> 50:45.007
Billy? A word.

50:45.009 --> 50:46.809
Sure thing.

50:46.811 --> 50:48.978
Brothers.
Appreciate it.

50:48.980 --> 50:50.546
What's goin' on?

50:53.517 --> 50:55.084
How do you have this?

50:55.086 --> 50:57.653
Why did you lie?
About what?

50:57.655 --> 51:00.623
- Why do you have this?
- Don't fuck with me, man.

51:00.625 --> 51:03.893
You said you didn't know Liz O'Neil,
but you have a picture of her.

51:03.895 --> 51:08.564
Brother Wayne,
this is Lyla, my wife.

51:08.566 --> 51:11.667
I know this woman as Lyla Rose.

51:11.669 --> 51:13.369
Where is she?
Why do you care?

51:13.371 --> 51:15.871
Because I do.

51:22.612 --> 51:25.381
[SIGHS]

51:26.550 --> 51:28.884
She fell hard, brother.

51:28.886 --> 51:31.320
Right on down the mountain.

51:31.322 --> 51:35.024
- You mean she left?
- I mean I kicked her drug-using ass out.

51:36.726 --> 51:38.828
Broke my heart to do it.

51:39.596 --> 51:40.963
Women.

51:40.965 --> 51:44.066
Why God made 'em such slippery
creatures I'll never know.

51:45.068 --> 51:46.969
Where'd she go?

51:46.971 --> 51:52.108
Who knows? Her mama's dead,
and never really had a daddy.

51:52.110 --> 51:54.443
Her mama ain't dead.
Sure, she is.

51:54.445 --> 51:56.512
Been dead for years.

51:56.514 --> 51:59.081
All she got left
is her sister, Charlotte.

52:01.485 --> 52:03.886
Or should I say Rachel?

52:06.923 --> 52:10.659
Why don't you go ask your daughter
what happened to her sister?

52:10.661 --> 52:13.996
Watch that forked tongue slide
right out of her fuckin' mouth.

52:13.998 --> 52:15.898
Excuse me.

52:26.243 --> 52:27.943
Is your mom dead?

52:27.945 --> 52:29.512
What?

52:31.181 --> 52:33.182
How do you know that?

52:39.623 --> 52:42.191
What did he say?

52:43.260 --> 52:44.994
Wayne, what did Billy say?

52:46.796 --> 52:49.865
- [BELL TOLLING]
- Wayne, what did Billy say?

52:50.634 --> 52:52.501
Look, I know that I lied, but...

52:52.503 --> 52:54.570
I was desperate, okay?

52:54.572 --> 52:58.007
I fucked up.
What'd he say about Liz?

52:58.009 --> 53:00.309
You know you can't trust them.

53:00.311 --> 53:02.278
Wayne!

53:06.116 --> 53:08.918
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

53:15.292 --> 53:16.892
[WHIMPERS]

53:16.894 --> 53:19.695
[BROTHER BILLY] The Lord knows what
we're doing up on this mountain.

53:19.697 --> 53:21.830
[CONGREGANTS AFFIRMING]

53:21.832 --> 53:25.000
He knows!
[MAN] Yeah, he does.

53:25.002 --> 53:26.602
He knows we ain't lookin' to die.

53:26.604 --> 53:28.771
[CONGREGANTS AFFIRMING]

53:28.773 --> 53:32.408
- We're lookin' to live!
- [TOGETHER] Yeah!

53:40.584 --> 53:42.518
[GASPS]

53:42.520 --> 53:44.553
Stop it!

53:45.522 --> 53:47.456
[GASPS]

53:47.458 --> 53:49.458
<i>[BROTHER BILLY]</i>
<i>We're lookin' for redemption...</i>

53:49.460 --> 53:51.760
[CONGREGANTS AFFIRMING]

53:51.762 --> 53:53.596
in his name.

53:53.598 --> 53:56.065
Brother Cole, get on up here
so we can pray on you.

54:08.745 --> 54:12.047
We know you have
the power, Lord Jesus.

54:12.049 --> 54:14.283
We know you have the power.

54:14.285 --> 54:16.118
[BROTHER COLE GRUNTING]

54:16.120 --> 54:17.987
We ask you to heal this man.

54:19.589 --> 54:21.156
Cure him of his cancer.

54:21.158 --> 54:23.592
[BROTHER COLE GRUNTING]

54:23.594 --> 54:25.995
We ask you to purify his body...

54:26.730 --> 54:28.998
and strengthen his heart...

54:29.000 --> 54:30.566
for the battle to come!

54:30.568 --> 54:33.035
Butch, bring it on.

54:33.037 --> 54:36.639
♪♪ [ROCK]

54:36.641 --> 54:38.574
[BILLY GROANING]
Come on.

54:38.576 --> 54:41.010
- ♪ And I'm on my way to heaven ♪
- Come on!

54:41.012 --> 54:43.679
We got you, brother.
We got you, Brother Cole.

54:43.681 --> 54:46.115
[BROTHER BILLY GRUNTING]

54:48.518 --> 54:50.419
[WOMAN] Praise the Lord!

55:07.604 --> 55:09.204
Hey!

55:09.206 --> 55:11.140
What do you know?

55:11.142 --> 55:12.775
Come back!

55:15.645 --> 55:17.479
Come back!

55:20.583 --> 55:22.318
[GASPS]

55:25.422 --> 55:28.657
♪♪ [CONTINUES]

55:47.177 --> 55:49.745
[RATTLING]

56:18.641 --> 56:20.676
[SHOUTING]
Ow!

56:20.678 --> 56:23.278
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

56:25.181 --> 56:26.915
[WOMAN] Oh, my God!

56:38.161 --> 56:39.962
Save him, Jesus.
Save him!

56:55.078 --> 56:57.646
What are you doing out here,

56:57.648 --> 56:59.948
Charlotte?

57:02.352 --> 57:04.052
How do you know my name?

57:04.054 --> 57:06.989
Lyla...
she talked about you all the time.

57:08.358 --> 57:10.426
Lyla?
Your sister.

57:10.428 --> 57:12.294
Brother Wayne pulled out
that photo,

57:12.296 --> 57:15.397
and it was like a shroud had
been lifted from my eyes,

57:15.399 --> 57:18.000
and I could see you.

57:24.707 --> 57:27.142
Is she here?

57:38.421 --> 57:40.622
[HEAVY BREATHING, COUGHING]

57:46.763 --> 57:49.097
[COUGHING]

57:54.938 --> 57:57.239
[WHEEZING]

58:20.864 --> 58:22.431
Go on.

58:34.577 --> 58:37.713
- Where is she?
- She's gone.

58:37.715 --> 58:41.683
Back in the gutter
where I found her.

58:41.685 --> 58:44.853
You comin' here was never
about your sister, Charlotte.

58:44.855 --> 58:46.421
It was always about you.

58:48.391 --> 58:50.926
Your sins.

58:50.928 --> 58:53.896
And your need to be
forgiven for what you did.

59:10.780 --> 59:12.748
On your knees.

59:40.009 --> 59:41.977
You got a demon
inside you, Charlotte.

59:42.946 --> 59:44.813
Just like your sister.

59:44.815 --> 59:47.382
Except your demon's name is guilt,

59:47.384 --> 59:49.384
and we gotta get it out.

59:50.453 --> 59:52.588
- [WHIP CRACKS]
- [CRIES OUT]

59:55.625 --> 59:58.527
[BROTHER BILLY] We talked for
hours, your sister and I.

01:00:00.129 --> 01:00:02.130
Right in this very room.

01:00:02.132 --> 01:00:04.299
She told me everything.
[SOBBING]

01:00:06.035 --> 01:00:08.737
- And it was all your fault.
- [WHIP CRACKS]

01:00:09.739 --> 01:00:12.474
And you wanted her to fall.
No.

